§§ Notation ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ We denote the line through $x$ and $y$ by $L(x,y)$. ⦉
⦉

§ Properties ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ There are a few nice properties. ⦉

  ‖ If $x ≠ y$, then $L(x, y) = L(y, x)$. ⦉

  ‖ Also, if $v$ and $w$ are in $L(x, y)$ and $v ≠ w$, then
    the line through $v$ and $w$ is the same as the line
    through $x$ and $y$. ⦉

  ‖ In symbols
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ L(v, w) = L(x, y) ⦉
    ⦉⦉
⦉

